I. Preamble
Everything starts somewhere, though many physicists disagree. But people have always been
dimly aware of the problem with the start of things. They wonder how the snowplough driver
gets to work, or how the makers of dictionaries look up the spelling of words. (Terry Pratchett,
Hogfather)
Welcome, dear women (and confused, curious, or nosy men), to this weird and wonderful corner of the
internet that could be called a ‚ÄúDate-Me Doc‚Äù by a certain group of people who think that such a name
sounds cute, fun, or flirty. I am not such a person; nor is it my intention to write in a cute, fun, or flirty
manner (at least in the sense that most people would understand those terms). My purposes in writing this
document are threefold:
1. To get my thoughts on a page that I might better process them for my own personal benefit.
2. To share these thoughts with others, so that they might enrich their own ideas concerning
dating.
3. To find, whether through divine intervention or the small ghost of a random chance, a
woman interested in exploring whether we might possess such complementary traits and
characteristics that a life-long partnership would be favorable.
I ask that you, the reader, would keep an open mind as you read this treatise. Ruminate on complex ideas.
Reread what is unclear. Try to really understand the man behind the Logitech K845 keyboard, and please,
do not be frightened by my facetious manner of writing. (It‚Äôs just a defense mechanism; I promise.) If you
manage to make it all the way to the end, I tip my non-existent hat to you.
